= LITERATURE REVIEW

== Existing Systems
The landscape of email communication has shifted from simple message exchange to complex productivity ecosystems. While traditional clients focus on stability and broad feature sets, modern "power-user" clients prioritize speed and artificial intelligence. This section analyzes the leading global solutions to establish a benchmark for the CDC Investor Connect application.

=== Enterprise Industry Standards: Gmail & Microsoft Outlook
- *Gmail:* Known for its powerful search capabilities and deep integration with Google Workspace. It pioneered "Smart Compose" and "Tabbed Categories" (Primary, Social, Promotions). However, for high-stakes investor relations, users often find its interface "cluttered" and prone to distractions from non-essential automated mail.

- *Microsoft Outlook:* The standard for "locked-down" organizations. Its strength lies in its robust calendar integration and enterprise-grade security (S/MIME). For the CDC, Outlook is often the primary backend provider; however, its mobile interface is frequently criticized for being heavy and unintuitive for rapid, on-the-go data entry like contact scanning.

While these platforms are reliable for data storage, they are "general purpose" and do not offer specialized workflows for managing investment leads or regional administrative tasks.

=== High-Productivity & AI-Driven Clients: Superhuman & Spark

To address "email fatigue," a new category of email apps has emerged, focusing on speed and minimal design.

*Superhuman:* Widely considered the fastest email experience in the world. It utilizes a "keyboard-first" philosophy and a "Split Inbox" to separate human-sent emails from automated notifications. Its most relevant feature to this project is *AI-powered follow-ups,* which remind users to nudge a contact if they haven't replied.

*Spark Mail:* Developed by Readdle, Spark focuses on "Smart Categorization" and team collaboration. Its main feature allows users to screen new senders, a valuable concept for government officials who may receive high volumes of unsolicited inquiries. Unlike Superhuman's high subscription cost, Spark offers a more accessible model but lacks the ultra-minimalist focus required for maximum executive speed.

=== Specialized Features: CRM & Contact Integration
Apps like *Salesforce Anywhere* and *HubSpot Mobile* allow users to scan business cards to create CRM entries. These tools are the inspiration for the Contact ID Scanning module in the CDC app. However, these are often paid, proprietary platforms that do not integrate natively with the specific ID formats or the private server infrastructure required by the Cambodian government.
